The paper deals with face reconstruction using convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also involves rendering and generating photo-realistic face images, which falls under computer graphics (cs.GR). The use of video-type adjacent frame pairs suggests that the paper may also belong to multimedia (cs.MM). The proposed learning framework involves training convolutional networks, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
